{"id":45017,"date":"2019-01-25T19:11:38","date_gmt":"2019-01-25T16:11:38","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/?p=45017"},"modified":"2019-01-26T18:20:10","modified_gmt":"2019-01-26T16:20:10","slug":"head-of-bulgarian-construction-control-with-large-waterfront-apartment-registered-to-his-mother-in-law","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/en\/head-of-bulgarian-construction-control-with-large-waterfront-apartment-registered-to-his-mother-in-law.html","title":{"rendered":"Head of Bulgarian Construction Control with Large Waterfront Apartment Registered to His Mother-in-Law"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>In 2002, Veselin Tsolevski paid only BGN 17,300 for an\napartment of 68 square meters on the waterfront in the town of Sozopol on the\nsouthern Bulgarian Black Sea coast. The seller was the construction company <a href=\"https:\/\/tr.bivol.bg\/view.php?guid=121352575\">BDK<\/a> Ltd. The apartment,\nhowever, had one disadvantage &#8211; it did not have a direct view of the sea. But\nthis injustice turned out reparable. In 2010, <a href=\"https:\/\/tr.bivol.bg\/view.php?guid=131208694\">BDK Invest<\/a>, with the\nsame owners, offered to Mr Tzolevski, who was already 82, to exchange the\napartment for another, larger one &#8211; 97.8 square meters in a cozy villa with a\nterrace and a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.google.bg\/maps\/@42.4077317,27.7091886,3a,60y,122.14h,86.21t\/data=!3m6!1e1!3m4!1sWi5y1FqPTmdgF_Ssf8goQw!2e0!7i13312!8i6656\">wonderful\nview<\/a> of the bay.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul data-carousel-extra='{\"blog_id\":1,\"permalink\":\"https:\\\/\\\/bivol.bg\\\/en\\\/head-of-bulgarian-construction-control-with-large-waterfront-apartment-registered-to-his-mother-in-law.html\"}' class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img data-attachment-id=\"44985\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/en\/head-of-bulgarian-construction-control-with-large-waterfront-apartment-registered-to-his-mother-in-law.html\/tust-2010-2-2\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2010-1.png\" data-orig-size=\"1854,1126\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"tust-2010\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2010-1-300x182.png\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2010-1-1024x622.png\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"622\" src=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2010-1-1024x622.png\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"44985\" data-link=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/en\/tust-2010-2-2\" class=\"wp-image-44985\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2010-1-1024x622.png 1024w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2010-1-300x182.png 300w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2010-1-768x466.png 768w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2010-1-1170x711.png 1170w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2010-1-585x355.png 585w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2010-1.png 1854w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><figcaption>Swap in 2010<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img data-attachment-id=\"44988\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/en\/head-of-bulgarian-construction-control-with-large-waterfront-apartment-registered-to-his-mother-in-law.html\/tust-2002-17300-2-2\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2002-17300-1.png\" data-orig-size=\"1284,794\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"tust-2002-17300\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2002-17300-1-300x186.png\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2002-17300-1-1024x633.png\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"633\" src=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2002-17300-1-1024x633.png\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"44988\" data-link=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/en\/tust-2002-17300-2-2\" class=\"wp-image-44988\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2002-17300-1-1024x633.png 1024w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2002-17300-1-300x186.png 300w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2002-17300-1-768x475.png 768w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2002-17300-1-1170x724.png 1170w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2002-17300-1-585x362.png 585w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/tust-2002-17300-1.png 1284w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><figcaption>Acquisition in 2002<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The reason for this generosity towards the elderly man and\nhis wife can hardly be explained by the principles of the free market, but\nthere are other principles. The son-in-law of the now-late Mr Tsolevski is <strong>architect Ivan Nestorov<\/strong>, the current Director\nof the Directorate for National Construction Control (DNSK), who has previously\nheld other senior State and municipal posts related to construction control.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Precisely, in 2002, when his father-in-law, Tsolevski, bought\nprofitably the first apartment, architect Nestorov was already a high-ranking official\nat the DNSK. And in 2010, when the swap happened, Ivan Nestorov was already the\nHead of the Architecture and Urban Planning Directorate of Sofia Municipality\n(City Hall), appointed there in 2006 by the then-Mayor (and current third-term\nPrime Minister) Boyko Borisov. Before this, for a short time, he was an acting Chief\nArchitect of Sofia.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"504\" src=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/nestorov-sozopol-1024x504.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-45000\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/nestorov-sozopol-1024x504.png 1024w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/nestorov-sozopol-300x148.png 300w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/nestorov-sozopol-768x378.png 768w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/nestorov-sozopol-1170x576.png 1170w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/nestorov-sozopol-1920x946.png 1920w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/nestorov-sozopol-585x288.png 585w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>According to the Property Register, the company &#8220;BDK\nInvest&#8221; had serious construction sites in Sofia at the time Nestorov was\nthe Director of &#8220;Architecture and Urban Planning&#8221;.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>After his career in the Sofia Municipality, Nestorov was\ntransferred to Ministry of Regional Development and Public Works, where he\nbecame Director of the Geological Protection and Urban Development Directorate.\nConsidering that most of the BDK construction sites in Sozopol are on the\nwaterfront and are often erected directly on the rocks, the investment in the\nfather-in-law\u2019s apartment looks well calculated and prescient.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>After being appointed as Head of the DNSK in 2017, replacing\nMilka Gecheva, Ivan Nestorov has submitted a completely \u201cvirgin\u201d <a href=\"https:\/\/register.caciaf.bg\/2018\/9BD0180A-6E40-418E-8C37-E901F07024D892906.xml\">property\ndeclaration<\/a>, as suits a conscientious civil servant who lives on wages and\ndoes now own a home or a bank account. Income from salaries \u2013 BGN 33,766 and not\na penny more.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>And a cheap apartment in Sofia from another construction company<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In 2005, the mother-in-law of architect Nestorov, Zdravka\nTsolevska, secured another gainful property acquisition. She bought an\napartment of 92 square meters in the capital Sofia for only BGN 47,500. The\nseller was the construction company &#8220;Beta Iv Delta&#8221;.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul data-carousel-extra='{\"blog_id\":1,\"permalink\":\"https:\\\/\\\/bivol.bg\\\/en\\\/head-of-bulgarian-construction-control-with-large-waterfront-apartment-registered-to-his-mother-in-law.html\"}' class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img data-attachment-id=\"44991\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/en\/head-of-bulgarian-construction-control-with-large-waterfront-apartment-registered-to-his-mother-in-law.html\/beta-iv-47500-2\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-47500.png\" data-orig-size=\"1232,730\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"beta-iv-47500\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-47500-300x178.png\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-47500-1024x607.png\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"607\" src=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-47500-1024x607.png\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"44991\" data-link=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/en\/beta-iv-47500-2\" class=\"wp-image-44991\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-47500-1024x607.png 1024w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-47500-300x178.png 300w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-47500-768x455.png 768w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-47500-1170x693.png 1170w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-47500-585x347.png 585w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-47500.png 1232w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><figcaption>Nestorov&#8217;s mother-in-law buys 90 square meters for BGN 47,500 <\/figcaption><\/figure><\/li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img data-attachment-id=\"44994\" data-permalink=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/en\/head-of-bulgarian-construction-control-with-large-waterfront-apartment-registered-to-his-mother-in-law.html\/beta-iv-162000-2\" data-orig-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-162000.png\" data-orig-size=\"1376,760\" data-comments-opened=\"0\" data-image-meta=\"{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}\" data-image-title=\"beta-iv-162000\" data-image-description=\"\" data-medium-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-162000-300x166.png\" data-large-file=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-162000-1024x566.png\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"566\" src=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-162000-1024x566.png\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"44994\" data-link=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/en\/beta-iv-162000-2\" class=\"wp-image-44994\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-162000-1024x566.png 1024w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-162000-300x166.png 300w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-162000-768x424.png 768w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-162000-1170x646.png 1170w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-162000-585x323.png 585w, https:\/\/bivol.bg\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/beta-iv-162000.png 1376w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><figcaption>The same company sells similar apartments for three times more<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>A reference in the Property Register shows that a similar\napartment in the same building, but with a smaller area, was sold by the same\ncompany only a month earlier, for three times more &#8211; BGN 162,139.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Bivol contacted the DNSK press office and asked a question\nto Mr. Nestorov whether he considered that the lucrative property acquisitions\nof his in-laws could put him in a situation of conflict of interest because at\nthe time of the purchases he had exercised oversight on construction companies.\nWe did not get a call by the time of the publication of this article, but we\nare ready to give him the right of reply and publish everything he has to say.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>In 2002, Veselin Tsolevski paid only BGN 17,300 for an apartment of 68 square meters on the waterfront in the town of Sozopol on the southern Bulgarian Black Sea coast.&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":f